  "page": 187,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0002",
      "text": " 168",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0003",
      "text": "6.6.5.6.2  ACK_0 capability",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        221.98,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0004",
      "text": "0 = ACK_0 incapable",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        190.15,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0005",
      "text": "1 = ACK_0 capable",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        94.97,
        182.34,
        106.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0006",
      "text": "The ACK_0 capability bit (word 1, bit 31) specifies that the Nx_Port supplying these Class Service",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        539.9,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0007",
      "text": "Parameters may or may not be capable of support for ACK_0 as a Sequence Recipient for acknowl-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        540.11,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0008",
      "text": "edgement of an entire Sequence in either Discard or Process Exchange Error Policies.  As a Se-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        540.14,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0009",
      "text": "quence Recipient an Nx_Port shall support infinite buffering and be capable of transmitting ACK_0",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        154.96,
        539.99,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0010",
      "text": "frames in response to Data frame transmission.  ACK_0 support is applicable to acknowledged class",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        539.96,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0011",
      "text": "of service Sequences (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        178.96,
        260.9,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0012",
      "text": "The conditions under which ACK_0 is supported are defined in table 168 and described in the follow-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        202.96,
        540.03,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0013",
      "text": "ing text. ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        214.96,
        133.77,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0014",
      "text": "If one Nx_Port (e.g., Nx_Port A) is capable of receiving ACK_0 as a Sequence Initiator (Word 0, Bit",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        540.02,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0015",
      "text": "11 set to one) and the other Nx_Port (e.g., Nx_Port B) is capable of transmitting ACK_0 as a Se-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        540.22,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0016",
      "text": "quence Recipient (Word 1, Bit 31 set to one), then ACK_0 may be used when Nx_Port A is the Se-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.96,
        539.99,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0017",
      "text": "quence Initiator and Nx_Port B is the Sequence Recipient.  Otherwise, ACK_0 shall not be supported",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        539.95,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0018",
      "text": "while Nx_Port A is the Sequence Initiator and Nx_Port B is the Sequence Recipient.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        466.59,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0019",
      "text": "ACK_0 capability may be asymmetrical for a single Nx_Port (i.e., an Nx_Port may be capable pro-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        442.96,
        540.1,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0020",
      "text": "cessing ACK_0 as a Sequence Initiator, but not be capable of ACK_0 transmission as a Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        539.97,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0021",
      "text": "Recipient.  Similarly, an Nx_Port may be capable of generating ACK_0 as a Sequence Recipient, but",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        466.96,
        540.04,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0022",
      "text": "not be capable of ACK_0 reception as a Sequence Initiator).  If an Nx_Port sets both Word 0, bit 11",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        539.95,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0023",
      "text": "and Word 1, bit 31 to one, then it is capable of ACK_0 support as either a Sequence Initiator or a Se-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        540.07,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0024",
      "text": "quence Recipient.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.96,
        176.0,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0025",
      "text": "6.6.5.6.3  X_ID interlock",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        207.07,
        538.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0026",
      "text": "0 = X_ID interlock not required",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        231.17,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0027",
      "text": "1 = X_ID interlock required",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        214.51,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0028",
      "text": "X_ID interlock (word 1, bit 29)",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        586.96,
        226.7,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0029",
      "text": "only applies to Class 1 and Class 2.  This bit indicates that the Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        229.32,
        586.96,
        539.97,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 3
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0030",
      "text": "supplying this parameter requires that an interlock be used during X_ID assignment in Class 1 and 2.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        540.07,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0031",
      "text": "In X_ID assignment, the Sequence Initiator shall set the Recipient X_ID value to FFFFh in the first",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        539.99,
        622.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0032",
      "text": "Data frame of a Sequence and the Recipient shall supply its X_ID in the ACK frame corresponding to",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        540.07,
        634.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0033",
      "text": "the first Data frame of a Sequence.  The Sequence Initiator shall not transmit additional frames until",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        634.96,
        540.08,
        646.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0034",
      "text": "the corresponding ACK is received.  Following reception of the ACK, the Sequence Initiator continues",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        539.97,
        658.14
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p187_s0035",
      "text": "transmission of the Sequence using both assigned X_ID values (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        445.39,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
